I've added the lazy explanation to the pull request description as well.

If someone really wants to test the lengthy explanation, it is possible. I did that with `FUZZ=utxo_total_supply ./bld-cmake/src/test/fuzz/fuzz -runs=2` and a small diff to peek into the global PRNG state. The expected result should be that a constant string is printed twice.


```diff
diff --git a/src/test/util/setup_common.cpp b/src/test/util/setup_common.cpp
index 3f8c6f41ba..771cf0e436 100644
--- a/src/test/util/setup_common.cpp
+++ b/src/test/util/setup_common.cpp
@@ -148,7 +148,8 @@ BasicTestingSetup::BasicTestingSetup(const ChainType chainType, TestOpts opts)
         // tests, such as the fuzz tests to run in several processes at the
         // same time, add a random element to the path. Keep it small enough to
         // avoid a MAX_PATH violation on Windows.
-        const auto rand{HexStr(g_rng_temp_path.randbytes(10))};
+        const auto rand{HexStr(m_rng.randbytes(10))};
+        std::cout << rand << std::endl;
         m_path_root = fs::temp_directory_path() / TEST_DIR_PATH_ELEMENT / test_name / rand;
         TryCreateDirectories(m_path_root);
